The following example:
```scala
class U {
  def f[T](x:T):T=x
}
object H extends Application {
  val u=new U
  val z:Int=(u.f _)(4)
  println("done")
}
```
results in:
```scala
java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: H$$$$anonfun$$1.apply(I)I
```

Replacing `u.f` with `u.f[Int]` works ok; possibly related are scala/bug#1317 and scala/bug#1570.
